Examples
===============================================================================

Examples are runnable material for the current release.

The examples tree should be organized by what an example demonstrates, not by whether it is considered `working` or `aspirational`.

1. Current user-facing examples
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Language examples currently include:

```text
examples/working/fizzbuzz.mec
examples/working/bubble-sort.mec
examples/working/n-body.mec
examples/working/ekf.mec
examples/working/factorial.mec
```

Browser project examples include:

```text
examples/analog-clock/
```

Robot arm examples live with the host crate:

```text
hosts/robot-arm/examples/
```

2. Target organization
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Future example organization should use categories like:

```text
examples/language/
examples/hosts/
examples/runtime/
examples/machines/
examples/experimental/
```

Do not add new top-level loose examples. If an example needs multiple files, put it in a folder with a README.

3. Test fixtures
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Files that exist only to exercise tests should live under test fixtures, not as top-level user-facing examples.
